Module atu.software

Package ie.atu.sw

package ie.atu.sw
  • Class
    Description
    AudioClip
    This class allows you to play audio files in the game, such as *.wav files.
    Direction
    The enum Direction defines the 4 directions of movement in the game and assigns a number to each.
    GameObject
    This is the GameObject for entity's such as the Player or Spider, game engines such as Unity take a similar approach, with each GameObject in the game having a start and update method
    GameObjectable
    Interface for a GameObject, implement the methods below, and you can be a GameObject too!
    GameObjectStore
    GameObjectStore is used to store the GameObject in the game.
    GameView
    Class that implements the game view for the game, handles key press events and game loop.
    GameView.Builder
    This class will help you building an instance of GameView.
    Player
    Class for the Player character in the game.
    Position
    Position represents a position in a 2D coordinate system.
    Renderer
    This class is dedicated to rendering stuff to the screen, you need to provide your own Graphics2D context.
    Runner
    This class starts that game, creates an instance of GameView.
    Spider
    Class for the Spider in the game.
    Sprite
    This class represents a sprite, which is an image that can be rendered on the screen.
    TileMatrix
    TileMatrix encapsulates the byte matrix, and array of Sprite for that tile matrix.
